kevin's math library (very original name, yes, i know.)
(c) 1996-2002 Kevin Meinert


Usage:
=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-

everything is in the kev namespace:

kev::Quat         (templated for any datatype)
kev::Vec2         (templated for any datatype)
kev::Vec3         (templated for any datatype)
kev::Vec4         (templated for any datatype)
kev::Matrix4f     
kev::ColorRGBA

the template ones have typedefs for what they are (i.e. kev::Vec3f)

Defines.h 
defines a math portability layer (ie. kev::sin()), and common constants

convert.h 
supplies conversion funcs between the data types

extend.h
adds funcs that don't nessesarily belong in the classes...



history:
=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-
originally started 1996 as f-lib (everything was prefixed by an f, no reason)
progressed rapidly in Iowa State Univiersity's computer graphics class (ME519)
progressed from there in various little prototype projects Ive done for amusement

